# Environment Configuration for Raid Always More WoW Guild Recruitment App
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in the values

# ====================
# Application Settings
# ====================
NODE_ENV=development
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_NAME="Raid Always More"
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_DESCRIPTION="Formulaire de recrutement pour la guilde WoW Raid Always More"
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_ENABLED=true

# ====================
# Security & Authentication
# ====================
ADMIN_SECRET=your-super-secret-admin-key-change-this-in-production
BCRYPT_SALT_ROUNDS=12
ARGON2_SALT_LENGTH=16
ARGON2_HASH_LENGTH=32
ARGON2_TIME_COST=3
ARGON2_MEMORY_COST=4096

# ====================
# Database Configuration
# ====================
# Choose one database option:

# Option 1: PostgreSQL (Recommended for production)
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://username:password@localhost:5432/raid_always_more

# Option 2: Supabase
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# Option 3: SQLite (Development only)
# DATABASE_URL=file:./data/dev.db

# ====================
# Session & Cookies
# ====================
SESSION_SECRET=your-session-secret-key-change-this
COOKIE_SECURE=false # Set to true in production with HTTPS
COOKIE_SAMESITE=lax
COOKIE_MAX_AGE=86400 # 24 hours in seconds

# ====================
# Admin Demo Credentials (Development Only)
# ====================
# For demo purposes only - in production, use a real authentication system
ADMIN_DEMO_USERNAME=admin
ADMIN_DEMO_PASSWORD=demo123

# ====================
# Rate Limiting
# ====================
RATE_LIMIT_MAX_REQUESTS=100
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=900000 # 15 minutes

# ====================
# Logging
# ====================
LOG_LEVEL=info # debug, info, warn, error
ENABLE_REQUEST_LOGGING=true

# ====================
# Email Notifications (Future Feature)
# ====================
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
# SMTP_PASSWORD=your-app-password
# NOTIFICATION_EMAIL=admin@raid-always-more.com

# ====================
# Discord Integration
# ====================
# DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL=https://discord.com/api/webhooks/...
# DISCORD_GUILD_ID=your-guild-id
# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=your-bot-token

# ====================
# Development Overrides
# ====================
# Set to true to bypass authentication in development
DEVELOPMENT_SKIP_AUTH=false
# Set to true to enable mock data
ENABLE_MOCK_DATA=false

# ====================
# Build Configuration
# ====================
# Next.js build optimization
NEXT_TELEMETRY_DISABLED=1
```

This `.env.example` file provides:
1. **Clear sections** for different configuration areas
2. **Comprehensive coverage** of all potential environment variables needed
3. **Detailed comments** explaining each variable
4. **Default values** that work for development
5. **Placeholders** for production values that need to be changed
6. **Future feature** variables commented out for easy enablement
7. **Security warnings** for sensitive values

To use this file:
1. Copy to `.env.local` for local development
2. Fill in the actual values (especially security-related ones)
3. For production deployment (Hostinger), use their environment variable configuration panel to set these values

Important notes for Hostinger deployment:
1. Set `NODE_ENV=production`
2. Change `ADMIN_SECRET` to a strong, random value
3. Set `COOKIE_SECURE=true` if using HTTPS
4. Configure a real database (PostgreSQL recommended)
5. Remove or disable demo credentials in production
